text: The 2020 Queensland state election was held on 31 October 2020 to elect all 93 members of the Queensland Legislative Assembly. It was conducted by the Electoral Commission of Queensland (ECQ). The incumbent Labor government, led by Premier Annastacia Palaszczuk, won a third term in government, opposed by the Liberal National Party (LNP), led by Deb Frecklington. ==Notes== ==References== Category:Elections in Queensland Category:2020 elections in Australia Category:2020s in Queensland
title: 2020 Queensland state election
